title.narrative: 5.4 COMMUNICATIONS & ADVOCACY

description.narrative: Communications Advocacy & Partnerships: UNICEF staff and partners are provided tools, guidance and resources for effective advocacy and partnerships on child rights issues with stakeholders, which contributes to Environmental Sustainability, Other Cross-Sectoral Programme Areas, Other Cross-Sectoral Programme Areas (Covid), Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Capacities of subnational institutions are enhanced for child-sensitive and participatory social policy planning to support vulnerable girls and boys.

description.narrative: Seizing the opportunity of the CRC 30th anniversary, the office developed and implemented an integrated advocacy roadmap sturdily linked to programmes and with strong involvement of children, young people and national partners. The process culminated with the government and parliament commitment renewal and the adoption of a new roadmap for children's rights 2021- 2030 during the Child rights national congress organized by National Observatory of Child Rights (ONDE) in partnership with UNICEF. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:15/01/2020
